originalText.text: Came in and found this family owned locksmith. They were super helpful made me all of my keys without any problems. I would highly recommend anybody looking for any locksmith or have their keys done to come in and check them out be supportive.

originalText.text: Expensive but good. I lost my keys around 10 PM on a Saturday night, and called CBS because they’re also on the Upper East Side. They arrived in about a half hour, and the guy was quick and efficient and professional. However, for 5 minutes of work and a $40 new lock (Mortise cylinder 7185SC1-03-KD), he charged me $350, and wouldn’t take a credit card. When I told him I didn’t carry $350 in cash, he insisted I go to the ATM to get it.  So, they are kind of pricey, and won’t take credit after hours, but the work was well done.

originalText.text: I am awful with constantly forgetting the keys to my apartment. Tired of having to wait outside all day for someone to let me in, or wake up my roommates in the middle the night, I recently called up Reliable, and I was back in my home within a matter of minutes. The prices are very decent, and they are incredibly fast and friendly. I now diligently bring my keys with me everywhere, but I know if I should ever run into a similar fix, Reliable is the best for the job. Definitely recommended.

originalText.text: Went to visit a friend in the city for a night of drinking and debauchery. Upon returning to his place we realized that he lost his keys. I was in no mood to traipse around the city back tracking through our night so I offered to pop for a locksmith. We called Reliable, got a reasonable estimate and had a locksmith at the apartment in about 30 minutes. Reliable showed up quickly worked discreetly and had us back in the apartment in just a few minutes saving me from a horrible reverse bar crawl
